# Kaggle: Measuring Progress Toward AGI - Cognitive Abilities

## Competition Overview

Google DeepMind launched a **hackathon** (not a traditional predict-a-target Kaggle competition) where you **design AI evaluations/benchmarks** — not train models. The goal is to build tests that measure how well frontier AI models perform on cognitive abilities that are currently poorly evaluated.

- **Competition Page:** [Kaggle - Measuring Progress Toward AGI](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/kaggle-measuring-agi)
- **Platform:** Kaggle Community Benchmarks
- **Organizer:** Google DeepMind

---

## The Framework: 10 Cognitive Abilities

DeepMind's paper identifies **10 cognitive abilities** important for general intelligence:

| #  | Ability              | Status                                  |
|----|----------------------|-----------------------------------------|
| 1  | Perception           | Well-evaluated already                  |
| 2  | Generation           | Well-evaluated already                  |
| 3  | Memory               | Well-evaluated already                  |
| 4  | Reasoning            | Well-evaluated already                  |
| 5  | Problem Solving      | Well-evaluated already                  |
| 6  | **Learning**         | **Evaluation gap — COMPETITION TRACK**  |
| 7  | **Metacognition**    | **Evaluation gap — COMPETITION TRACK**  |
| 8  | **Attention**        | **Evaluation gap — COMPETITION TRACK**  |
| 9  | **Executive Functions** | **Evaluation gap — COMPETITION TRACK** |
| 10 | **Social Cognition** | **Evaluation gap — COMPETITION TRACK**  |

You must design benchmarks for one or more of the **5 underserved tracks**.

